The paper focuses on scene text recognition and proposes a content-aware text super-resolution network to generate high-resolution images for better recognition performance. Therefore, it is most likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as text recognition, which suggests that it may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) and computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-categories. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and loss functions for training the network also suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves image processing techniques, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
